data.fullContent: Being admitted into the osteopathic medicine program at Florida State University is a competitive process. The school accepts students who are likely to succeed in the education program. As a prospective student, you will need to excel in academics, leadership, and community service. In order to make it into the program, you need to get excellent grades and get above-average scores on the pre-admissions test. The admissions committee wants to see that you are a strong leader and that you have accomplished a lot in life through your volunteer work, for example. If you want to get into the program, you must show that you are more than capable of putting all the courses together, which can be difficult for some people. It is a challenging program, but it is one of the best in the United States.
